                           <locus from="Tail" to="Tail">Bottom spine edge of left board</locus> bears a circular label with unidentified number <q>439/2</q>.
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc><binding notBefore="1750" notAfter="1825"><p>Bound in a European style without a flap (Type III binding per Déroche) with a quarter buff-coloured paper spine, European Stormont patterned marbled paper sides, and blue sprinkled edges.</p>
                     <decoNote type="binding"><p>Titled <q xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"><hi rend="italic">Kissahi Char Derwish</hi></q> (Tale of the Four Dervishes) in Latin script in black <material>ink</material> on the spine.</p></decoNote>                     
